txt.en: 'There is much to do to aid the people of the Eastemnet. Threats approach us from all sides, and those in power seem ignorant to the danger, or worse.\n\n'Go out and aid the good people of these lands and they shall, in time, return your favours.'
'There is still much to do, but I feel today has been a good day.'
There is much to do to aid the people of the Eastemnet.
People who need aid can be found primarily in Harwick, Cliving, Eaworth, and Snowbourn.\n\nYou have been asked to aid the people of the Eastemnet.
Inform <TBD > you have aided the Eastenmet
<TBD npc_rohan_east_endgame_daily_wrapper.wc> is in <TBD Town> in Sutcrofts.\n\nReport back that you have done what you can today to aid the people of the Eastenmet.
